quran[431]{c,v,t}:
  67,1,Blessed be He in Whose Hand is the dominion; and He is Able to do all things
  67,2,"Who has created death and life that He may test you which of you is best in deed. And He is the Almighty, the Oft-Forgiving"
  67,3,Who has created the seven heavens one above the other; you can see no fault in the creation of the Most Gracious. Then look again. Can you see any rifts
  67,4,"Then look again and yet again, your sight will return to you Khasi', and worn out"
  67,5,"And indeed We have adorned the nearest heaven with lamps, and We have made such lamps (as) missiles to drive away the Shayatin, and have prepared for them the torment of the blazing Fire"
  67,6,"And for those who disbelieve in their Lord is the torment of Hell, and worst indeed is that destination"
  67,7,"When they are cast therein, they will hear its Shahiq while it is simmering"
  67,8,"It almost bursts up with fury. Every time a group is cast therein, its keepers will ask: \"Did no warner come to you"
  67,9,"They will say: \"Yes, indeed a warner did come to us, but we rejected him and said: `Allah never sent down anything; you are only in great error"
  67,10,"And they will say: \"Had we but listened or used our intelligence, we would not have been among the dwellers of the blazing Fire"
  67,11,"Then they will confess their sin. So, away with the dwellers of the blazing Fire"
  67,12,"Verily, those who fear their Lord unseen, theirs will be forgiveness and a great reward"
  67,13,"And whether you keep your talk secret or disclose it, verily, He is the All-Knower of what is in the breasts"
  67,14,"Should not He Who has created know And He is the Most Kind and Courteous, All-Aware"
  67,15,He it is Who has made the earth subservient to you; so walk in the paths thereof and eat of His provision. And to Him will be the resurrection
  67,16,"Do you feel secure that He, Who is over the heaven, will not cause the earth to sink with you, and then it should quake"
  67,17,"Or do you feel secure that He, Who is over the heaven, will not send against you a Hasib Then you shall know how has been My warning"
  67,18,"And indeed those before them rejected, then how terrible was My reproach"
  67,19,"Do they not see the birds above them, spreading out their wings and folding them in None upholds them except the Most Gracious. Verily, He is the All-Seer of everything"
  67,20,Who is it besides the Most Gracious that can be an army to you to help you The disbelievers are in nothing but delusion
  67,21,"Who is it that can provide for you if He should withhold His provision Nay, but they continue to be in pride, and flee"
  67,22,"Is he who walks prone on his face, more rightly guided, or he who walks upright on a straight path"
  67,23,"Say: \"It is He Who has created you, and endowed you with hearing and seeing, and hearts. Little thanks you give"
  67,24,"Say: \"It is He Who has created you on the earth, and to Him shall you be gathered"
  67,25,"They say: \"When will this promise come to pass, if you are telling the truth"
  67,26,"Say: \"The knowledge is with Allah only, and I am only a plain warner"
  67,27,"But when they will see it approaching, the faces of those who disbelieve will be sad and grievous, and it will be said: \"This is what you were calling for"
  67,28,"Say: \"Tell me! If Allah destroys me, and those with me, or He bestows His mercy on us - who can save the disbelievers from a painful torment"
  67,29,"Say: \"He is the Most Gracious, in Him we believe, and upon Him we rely. So, you will come to know who it is that is in manifest error"
  67,30,"Say: \"Tell me! If (all) your water were to sink away, who then can supply you with flowing water"
  68,1,Nun. By the pen and by what they Yastur
  68,2,"You, by the grace of your Lord, are not insane"
  68,3,"And verily, for you will be reward that is not Mamnun"
  68,4,"And verily, you are on an exalted character"
  68,5,"You will see, and they will see"
  68,6,Which of you is afflicted with madness
  68,7,"Verily, your Lord is the best Knower of him who has gone astray from His path, and He is the best Knower of those who are guided"
  68,8,"So, do not obey the deniers"
  68,9,"They wish that you should compromise with them, so they (too) would compromise with you"
  68,10,And do not obey every Hallaf Mahin
  68,11,"A Hammaz, going about with Namim"
  68,12,"Hinderer of the good, transgressor, sinful"
  68,13,"Utul, and moreover Zanim"
  68,14,(He was so) because he had wealth and children
  68,15,"When Our Ayat are recited to him, he says: \"Tales of the men of old"
  68,16,We shall brand him on the snout (nose)
  68,17,"Verily, We have tried them as We tried the People of the Garden, when they swore to pluck the fruits in the morning"
  68,18,"Without saying: \"If Allah wills"
  68,19,Then there passed over it a Ta'if from your Lord while they were asleep
  68,20,"So by the morning, it became like As-Sarim"
  68,21,Then they called out (one to another as soon) as the morning broke
  68,22,"Saying: \"Go to your tilth in the morning, if you would pluck (the fruits)"
  68,23,"So they departed, and they were whispering"
  68,24,No poor person shall enter upon you into it today
  68,25,And they went in the morning with Hard Qadirin
  68,26,"But when they saw it, they said: \"Verily, we have gone astray"
  68,27,Nay! Indeed we are deprived
  68,28,"The Awsat among them said; \"Did I not tell you, `Why do you not Tusabbihun"
  68,29,"They said: \"Glory to Our Lord! Verily, we have been wrongdoers"
  68,30,"Then they turned one against another, blaming"
  68,31,"They said: \"Woe to us! Verily, we were Taghin"
  68,32,"We hope that our Lord will give us in exchange better than it. Truly, we hope in our Lord"
  68,33,"Such is the punishment, but truly, the punishment of the Hereafter is greater if they but knew"
  68,34,"Verily, for those who have Taqwa are Gardens of Delight with their Lord"
  68,35,Shall We then treat the Muslims like the criminals
  68,36,What is the matter with you How judge you
  68,37,Or have you a Book wherein you learn
  68,38,That you shall therein have all that you choose
  68,39,"Or have you oaths from Us, lasting until the Day of Judgement, that yours will be what you judge"
  68,40,"Ask them, which of them will stand as surety for that"
  68,41,"Or have they \"partners\" Then let them bring their \"partners\" if they are truthful"
  68,42,"The Day when the Shin shall be laid bare and they shall be called to prostrate themselves, but they shall not be able to do so"
  68,43,"Their eyes will be cast down and ignominy will cover them; they used to be called to prostrate themselves, while they were"
  68,44,Then leave Me alone with whoever denies this narration. We shall punish them gradually from directions they perceive not
  68,45,"And I will grant them a respite. Verily, My plan is strong"
  68,46,"Or is it that you ask them a wage, so that they are heavily burdened with debt"
  68,47,"Or that the Unseen is in their hands, so that they can write it down"
  68,48,"So, wait with patience for the decision of your Lord, and be not like the Companion of the Fish when he cried out (to Us) while he was Makzum"
  68,49,"Had not a grace from his Lord reached him, he would indeed have been (left in the stomach of the fish, but We forgave him), so he was cast off on the naked shore, while he was to be blamed"
  68,50,Then his Lord chose him and made him of the righteous
  68,51,"And verily, those who disbelieve would almost make you slip with their eyes (through hatred) when they hear the Reminder (the Qur'an), and they say: \"Verily, he is a madman"
  68,52,But it is nothing else than a Reminder to all the creatures (`Alamin)
  69,1,Al-Haqqah
  69,2,What is Al-Haqqah
  69,3,And what will make you know what Al-Haqqah is
  69,4,Thamud and `Ad denied the Qari`ah
  69,5,"As for Thamud, they were destroyed by the Taghiyah"
  69,6,"And as for `Ad, they were destroyed by a wind, Sarsar `Atiyah"
  69,7,"Which Allah imposed on them for seven nights and eight days Husum, so that you could see men lying toppled, as if they were trunks of date palms, Khawiyah"
  69,8,Do you see any remnants of them
  69,9,"And Fir`awn, and those before him, and the cities overthrown committed Al-Khati'ah"
  69,10,"And they disobeyed their Lord's Messenger, so He seized them with a punishment that was Rabiyah"
  69,11,"Verily, when the water rose beyond its limits, We carried you in the ship"
  69,12,That We might make it an admonition for you and that it might be retained by the retaining ears
  69,13,Then when the Trumpet will be blown with one blowing
  69,14,"And the earth and the mountains shall be removed from their places, and crushed with a single crushing"
  69,15,Then on that Day shall the Event occur
  69,16,"And the heaven will be rent asunder, for that Day it will be frail and torn up"
  69,17,"And the angels will be on its sides, and eight angels will, that Day, bear the Throne of your Lord above them"
  69,18,"That Day shall you be brought to Judgement, not a secret of you will be hidden"
  69,19,"Then as for him who will be given his Record in his right hand will say: \"Here! read my Record"
  69,20,"Surely, I did believe that I shall meet my account"
  69,21,"So, he shall be in a life, well-pleasing"
  69,22,In a lofty Paradise
  69,23,The fruits in bunches whereof will be low and near at hand
  69,24,Eat and drink at ease for that which you have sent on before you in days past
  69,25,"But as for him who will be given his Record in his left hand, will say: \"I wish that I had not been given my Record"
  69,26,And that I had never known how my account is
  69,27,Would that it had been my end
  69,28,My wealth has not availed me
  69,29,My power has gone from me
  69,30,"(It will be said): \"Seize him and fetter him"
  69,31,Then throw him in the blazing Fire
  69,32,Then fasten him on a chain whereof the length is seventy cubits
  69,33,"Verily, he used not to believe in Allah, the Most Great"
  69,34,And urged not the feeding of the poor
  69,35,"So, no friend has he here this Day"
  69,36,Nor any food except filth from Ghislin
  69,37,None will eat it except the Khati'un
  69,38,"So, I swear by whatsoever you see"
  69,39,And by whatsoever you see not
  69,40,That this is verily the word of an honored Messenger
  69,41,"It is not the word of a poet, little is that you believe"
  69,42,"Nor is it the word of a soothsayer, little is that you remember"
  69,43,This is the revelation sent down from the Lord of all that exists
  69,44,And if he had forged a false saying concerning Us
  69,45,We surely would have seized him by his right hand
  69,46,And then We certainly would have cut off Al-Watin from him
  69,47,And none of you could have prevented it from him
  69,48,"And verily, this is a Reminder for those who have Taqwa"
  69,49,"And verily, We know that there are some among you that deny"
  69,50,And indeed it will be an anguish for the disbelievers
  69,51,"And verily, it (this Qur'an) is an absolute truth with certainty"
  69,52,"So, glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  70,1,A questioner asked concerning a torment about to befall
  70,2,"Upon the disbelievers, which none can avert"
  70,3,"From Allah, the Lord of the ways of ascent"
  70,4,The angels and the Ruh ascend to Him in a Day the measure whereof is fifty thousand years
  70,5,"So be patient, with a good patience"
  70,6,"Verily, they see it (the torment) afar off"
  70,7,But We see it near
  70,8,The Day that the sky will be like the Al-Muhl
  70,9,And the mountains will be like `Ihn
  70,10,And no friend will ask a friend
  70,11,"Though they shall be made to see one another, the criminal would desire to ransom himself from the punishment of that Day by his children"
  70,12,And his wife and his brother
  70,13,And his Fasilah who sheltered him
  70,14,"And all that are in the earth, so that it might save him"
  70,15,"By no means! Verily, it will be the fire of Hell"
  70,16,Nazza`ah the Shawa
  70,17,Calling (all) such as turn their backs and turn away their faces
  70,18,And collect (wealth) and hide it (from spending it in the cause of Allah)
  70,19,"Verily, man was created very impatient"
  70,20,Apprehensive when evil touches him
  70,21,And suppressive when good touches him
  70,22,Except those who are devoted to Salah
  70,23,Those who with their Salah are Da'imun
  70,24,And those in whose wealth there is a recognized right
  70,25,"For the one who asks, and for the deprived"
  70,26,And those who believe in the Day of Recompense
  70,27,And those who fear the torment of their Lord
  70,28,"Verily, the torment of their Lord is that before which none can feel secure"
  70,29,And those who guard their private part (chastity)
  70,30,Except from their wives or their right hand possessions -- for (then) they are not blameworthy
  70,31,"But whosoever seeks beyond that, then it is those who are trespassers"
  70,32,And those who keep their trusts and covenants
  70,33,And those who stand firm in their testimonies
  70,34,"And those who are with their Salah, Yuhafizun"
  70,35,"Such shall dwell in the Gardens, honored"
  70,36,"So, what is the matter with those disbelievers, before you Muhti`in"
  70,37,"On the right and on the left, `Izin"
  70,38,Does every man of them hope to enter the Paradise of Delight
  70,39,"But no! Verily, We have created them out of that which they know"
  70,40,But no! I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests that surely We are Able
  70,41,To replace them by (others) better than them; and We are not to be outrun
  70,42,"So, leave them to plunge in vain talk and play about, until they meet their Day which they are promised"
  70,43,The Day when they will come out of the graves quickly as racing to a Nusub
  70,44,"With their eyes lowered in fear and humility, ignominy covering them (all over)! That is the Day which they were promised"
  71,1,"Verily, We sent Nuh to his people (saying): \"Warn your people before there comes to them a painful torment"
  71,2,"He said: \"O my people! Verily, I am a plain warner to you"
  71,3,"That you should worship Allah, and have Taqwa of Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive you of your sins and respite you to an appointed term. Verily, the term of Allah when it comes, cannot be delayed, if you but know"
  71,5,"He said: O my Lord! Verily, I have called to my people night and day"
  71,6,But all my calling added nothing but to (their) flight
  71,7,"And verily, every time I called unto them that You might forgive them, they thrust their fingers into their ears, covered themselves up with their garments, and persisted, and magnified themselves in pride"
  71,8,"Then verily, I called to them openly (aloud)"
  71,9,"Then verily, I proclaimed to them in public, and I have appealed to them in private"
  71,10,"I said (to them): Ask forgiveness from your Lord, verily, He is Oft-Forgiving"
  71,11,He will send rain to you Midrar
  71,12,"And give you increase in wealth and children, and bestow on you gardens and bestow on you rivers"
  71,13,"What is the matter with you, that you do not hope for any Waqar from Allah"
  71,14,While He has created you (in) Atwar (stages)
  71,15,See you not how Allah has created the seven heavens in tiers
  71,16,"And has made the moon a light therein, and made the sun a lamp"
  71,17,And Allah has brought you forth from the (dust of) earth
  71,18,"Afterwards He will return you into it (the earth), and bring you forth"
  71,19,And Allah has made for you the earth a wide expanse
  71,20,That you may go about therein in broad roads
  71,21,"Nuh said: \"My Lord! They have disobeyed me, and followed one whose wealth and children give him no increase but loss"
  71,22,And they have plotted a mighty plot
  71,23,"And they have said: `You shall not leave your gods, nor shall you leave Wadd, nor Suwa`, nor Yaghuth, and Ya`uq and Nasr"
  71,24,"And indeed they have led many astray. And (O Allah): `Grant no increase to the wrongdoers save error"
  71,25,"Because of their sins they were drowned, then were made to enter the Fire. And they found none to help them instead of Allah"
  71,26,"And Nuh said: \"My Lord! Leave not one of the disbelievers on the earth Dayyar"
  71,27,"If You leave them, they will mislead Your servants, and they will beget none but wicked disbelievers"
  71,28,"(My Lord! Forgive me, and my parents, and him who enters my home as a believer, and all the believing men and women. And to the wrongdoers grant You no increase but destruction!\") Allah says"
  72,1,"Say: \"It has been revealed to me that a group of Jinn listened. They said: `Verily, we have heard a wonderful Recitation"
  72,2,"It guides to the right path, and we have believed therein, and we shall never join anything with our Lord"
  72,3,"And He, exalted be the Jadd of our Lord, has taken neither a wife nor a son"
  72,4,And that the foolish among us used to utter against Allah that which was an enormity in falsehood
  72,5,"And verily, we thought that men and Jinn would not utter a lie against Allah"
  72,6,"And verily, there were men among mankind who took shelter with the males among the Jinn, but they increased them in Rahaq"
  72,7,"And they thought as you thought, that Allah will not send any Messenger"
  72,8,And we have sought to reach the heaven; but we found it filled with stern guards and flaming fires
  72,9,"And verily, we used to sit there in stations, to (steal) a hearing, but any who listens now will find a flaming fire watching him in ambush"
  72,10,"And we know not whether evil is intended for those on the earth, or whether their Lord intends for them guidance"
  72,11,"There are among us some that are righteous, and some the contrary; we are groups having different ways"
  72,12,"And we think that we cannot escape Allah in the earth, nor can we escape Him by flight"
  72,13,"And indeed when we heard the Guidance, we believed therein, and whosoever believes in his Lord shall have no fear, either of a decrease in the reward of his good deeds or an increase in the punishment for his sins"
  72,14,"And of us some are Muslims, and of us some are Al-Qasitun. And whosoever has embraced Islam, then such have sought the right path"
  72,15,"And as for the Qasitun, they shall be firewood for Hell"
  72,16,"If they had believed in Allah, and went on the way, We would surely have bestowed on them water in abundance"
  72,17,"That We might try them thereby. And whosoever turns away from the Reminder of his Lord, He will cause him to enter in a Sa`ad torment"
  72,18,"And the Masjids are for Allah, so invoke not anyone along with Allah"
  72,19,And when the servant of Allah stood up invoking Him in prayer they just made round him a dense crowd as if sticking one over the other
  72,20,"Say: \"I invoke only my Lord, and I associate none as partners along with Him"
  72,21,"Say: \"It is not in my power to cause you harm, or to bring you to the right path"
  72,22,"Say: \"None can protect me from Allah's punishment, nor can I find refuge except in Him"
  72,23,"(Mine is) but conveyance from Allah and His Messages, and whosoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger, then verily, for him is the fire of Hell, he shall dwell therein forever"
  72,24,"Till, when they see that which they are promised, then they will know who it is that is weaker concerning helpers and less important concerning numbers"
  72,25,"Say: \"I know not whether that which you are promised is near or whether my Lord will appoint for it a distant term"
  72,26,"The All-Knower of the Unseen, and He reveals to none His Unseen"
  72,27,"Except to a Messenger whom He has chosen, and then He makes a band of watching guards to march before him and behind him"
  72,28,"Till he knows that they have conveyed the Messages of their Lord. And He surrounds all that which is with them, and He keeps count of all things"
  73,1,O you wrapped up
  73,2,"Stand (to pray) all night, except a little"
  73,3,"Half of it or less than that, a little"
  73,4,Or a little more. And Rattil the Qur'an Tartil
  73,5,"Verily, We shall send down to you a Word Thaqil"
  73,6,"Verily, rising (Nashi'ah) at night is better for understanding and more suitable for speech (recitation)"
  73,7,"Verily, for you in the day is lengthy Sabh"
  73,8,And remember the Name of your Lord and (Tabattil) devote yourself to Him with complete devotion
  73,9,"Lord of the east and the west; La ilaha illa Huwa, so take Him as a trustee"
  73,10,"And be patient with what they say, and keep away from them in a good way"
  73,11,"And leave Me alone to deal with the deniers, those who are in possession of good things of life. And give them respite for a little"
  73,12,"Verily, with Us are Ankal, and Jahim"
  73,13,"And a food that chokes, and a painful torment"
  73,14,"On the Day when the earth and the mountains will (Tarjufu) shake, and the mountains will be a heap of sand poured out"
  73,15,"Verily, We have sent to you a Messenger to be a witness over you, as We did send a Messenger to Fir`awn"
  73,16,But Fir`awn disobeyed the Messenger; so We seized him with a severe punishment
  73,17,"Then how can you protect yourselves from the punishment, if you disbelieve, on a Day that will make the children gray-headed"
  73,18,Whereon the heaven will be cleft asunder His promise is certainly to be accomplished
  73,19,"Verily, this is an admonition, therefore whosoever wills, let him take a path to His Lord"
  73,20,"Verily, your Lord knows that you do stand a little less than two-thirds of the night, or half the night, or a third of the night, and also a party of those with you. And Allah measures the night and the day. He knows that you are unable to pray the whole night, so He has turned to you. So, recite you of the Qur'an as much as may be easy for you. He knows that there will be some among you sick, others traveling through the land, seeking of Allah's bounty, yet others fighting in Allah's cause. So recite as much of the Qur'an as may be easy"
  74,1,O you enveloped in garments
  74,2,Arise and warn
  74,3,And magnify your Lord
  74,4,And purify your garments
  74,5,And keep away from Ar-Rujz
  74,6,And give not a thing in order to have more
  74,7,And be patient for the sake of your Lord
  74,8,"Then, when the Naqur is sounded"
  74,9,"Truly, that Day will be a Hard Day"
  74,10,Far from easy for the disbelievers
  74,11,Leave Me alone (to deal) with whom I created lonely
  74,12,And then granted him resources in abundance
  74,13,And children attending
  74,14,And made life smooth and comfortable for him
  74,15,After all that he desires that I should give more
  74,16,"Nay! Verily, he has been opposing Our Ayat"
  74,17,I shall force him to Sa`ud
  74,18,"Verily, he thought and plotted"
  74,19,"So let him be cursed, how he plotted"
  74,20,"And once more let him be cursed, how he plotted"
  74,21,Then he thought
  74,22,Then he frowned and he looked in a bad tempered way
  74,23,"Then he turned back, and was proud"
  74,24,"Then he said: \"This is nothing but magic from that of old"
  74,25,This is nothing but the word of a human being
  74,26,I will cast him into Saqar
  74,27,And what will make you know (exactly) what Saqar is
  74,28,"It spares not, nor does it leave (anything)"
  74,29,Scorching for the humans
  74,30,Over it are nineteen
  74,31,"And We have set none but angels as guardians of the Fire. And We have fixed their number only as a trial for the disbelievers, in order that the People of the Scripture may arrive at a certainty and that the believers may increase in faith, and that no doubt may be left for the People of the Scripture and the believers, and that those in whose hearts is a disease and the disbelievers may say: \"What does Allah intend by this example\" Thus Allah leads astray whom He wills and guides whom He wills. And none can know the hosts of your Lord but He. And this is nothing but a reminder to mankind"
  74,32,Nay! And by the moon
  74,33,And by the night when it withdraws
  74,34,And by the dawn when it brightens
  74,35,"Verily, it is but one of the greatest (signs)"
  74,36,A warning to mankind
  74,37,"To any of you that chooses to go forward, or to remain behind"
  74,38,Every person is a pledge for what he has earned
  74,39,Except those on the Right
  74,40,In Gardens they will ask one another
  74,41,About criminals (and they will say to them)
  74,42,What has caused you to enter Hell
  74,43,"They will say: \"We were not of those who used to offer the Salah"
  74,44,Nor did we feed the poor
  74,45,And we used to speak falsehood with vain speakers
  74,46,And we used to deny the Day of Recompense
  74,47,Until Al-Yaqin came to us
  74,48,So no intercession of intercessors will be of any use to them
  74,49,Then what is wrong with them that they turn away from admonition
  74,50,As if they were wild donkeys
  74,51,Fleeing from a Qaswarah
  74,52,"Nay, everyone of them desires that he should be given pages spread out"
  74,53,Nay! But they fear not the Hereafter
  74,54,"Nay, verily, this is an admonition"
  74,55,"So, whosoever wills receives admonition from it"
  74,56,"And they will not receive admonition unless Allah wills; He is the One, deserving of the Taqwa and He is the One Who forgives"
  75,1,Nay! I swear by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,And nay! I swear by An-Nafs Al-Lawwamah
  75,3,Does man think that We shall not assemble his bones
  75,4,"Yes, We are able to put together in perfect order the tips of his fingers"
  75,5,Nay! Man desires to break out ahead of himself
  75,6,"He asks: \"When will be this Day of Resurrection"
  75,7,"So, when Bariqa the sight"
  75,8,And the moon will be eclipsed
  75,9,And the sun and moon will be joined together
  75,10,"On that Day man will say: \"Where (is the refuge) to flee"
  75,11,No! There is no refuge
  75,12,Unto your Lord will be the place of rest that Day
  75,13,"On that Day man will be informed of what he sent forward, and what he left behind"
  75,14,Nay! Man will be well informed about himself
  75,15,Though he may put forth his excuses
  75,16,Move not your tongue concerning to make haste therewith
  75,17,It is for Us to collect it and that it be recited
  75,18,"And when We have recited it to you, then follow its recitation"
  75,19,Then it is for Us to make it clear
  75,20,But no! Rather you love the present life of this world
  75,21,And neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,Some faces that Day shall be Nadirah
  75,23,Looking at their Lord
  75,24,And some faces that Day will be Basirah
  75,25,Thinking that some calamity is about to fall on them
  75,26,"Nay, when it rea- ches to the collarbones"
  75,27,"And it will be said: \"Who can cure him"
  75,28,And he will think that it was the parting
  75,29,And one shank will be joined with another shank
  75,30,The drive will be on that Day to your Lord
  75,31,"So, he neither believed nor prayed"
  75,32,"But on the contrary, he denied and turned away"
  75,33,Then he walked in conceit to his family admiring himself
  75,34,Woe to you! And then woe to you
  75,35,"Again, woe to you! And then woe to you"
  75,36,Does man think that he will be left neglected
  75,37,Was he not a Nutfah of semen emitted
  75,38,Then he became an `Alaqah; then shaped and fashioned in due proportion
  75,39,"And made of him two sexes, male and female"
  75,40,"Is it not so then, that He would be able to give life to the dead"
  76,1,"Has there not been over man a period of time, when he was not a thing worth mentioning"
  76,2,"Verily, We have created man from Nutfah Amshaj, in order to try him, so, We made him hearer and seer"
  76,3,"Verily, We guided him to the way, whether he be grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"Verily, We have prepared for the disbelievers iron chains, iron collars, and Sa`ir"
  76,5,"Verily, the Abrar (righteous believers) shall drink of a cup mixed with Kafur"
  76,6,"A spring wherefrom the servants of Allah will drink, causing it to gush forth abundantly"
  76,7,"They fulfill (their) vows, and they fear a Day whose evil will be wide-spreading"
  76,8,"And they give food, inspite of their love for it, to the poor, the orphan and the captive"
  76,9,"(Saying): \"We feed you seeking Allah's Face only. We wish for no reward, nor thanks from you"
  76,10,"Verily, We fear from our Lord a Day that is `Abus and Qamtarir"
  76,11,"So, Allah saved them from the evil of that Day, and gave them Nadrah (a light of beauty) and joy"
  76,12,"And their recompense shall be Paradise, and silken garments, because they were patient"
  76,13,"Reclining therein on raised couches, they will see there neither the excessive heat, nor the excessive cold"
  76,14,"And the shade thereof is close upon them, and the bunches of fruit thereof will hang low within their reach"
  76,15,And among them will be passed round vessels of silver and cups of crystal
  76,16,"(Qawarir) Crystal-clear, made of silver. They will determine the measure thereof"
  76,17,And they will be given to drink there of a cup (of wine) mixed with Zanjabil (ginger)
  76,18,"A spring there, called Salsabil"
  76,19,"And round about them will (serve) boys of everlasting youth. If you see them, you would think them scattered pearls"
  76,20,"And when you look there (in Paradise), you will see a delight (that cannot be imagined), and a great dominion"
  76,21,"Their garments will be of fine green silk, and Istabraq. They will be adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a purifying drink"
  76,22,"(And it will be said to them): \"Verily, this is a reward for you, and your endeavor has been accepted"
  76,23,"Verily, it is We Who have sent down the Qur'an to you by stages"
  76,24,"Therefore be patient with constancy to the command of your Lord, and obey neither a sinner nor a disbeliever among them"
  76,25,And remember the Name of your Lord every morning and afternoon
  76,26,"And during the night, prostrate yourself to Him, and glorify Him a long night through"
  76,27,"Verily, these love the present life of this world, and put behind them a heavy Day"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them, and We have made them of strong build. And when We will, We can replace them with others like them with a complete replacement"
  76,29,"Verily, this is an admonition, so whosoever wills, let him take a path to his Lord"
  76,30,"But you cannot will, unless Allah wills. Verily, Allah is Ever All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,He will admit to His mercy whom He wills and as for the wrongdoers -- He has prepared a painful torment
  77,1,By the Mursalat `Urfa
  77,2,The `Asifat `Asfa
  77,3,And the Nashirat Nashra
  77,4,The Fariqat that separate
  77,5,The Mulqiyat that remind
  77,6,Excusing or warning
  77,7,"Surely, what you are promised will occur"
  77,8,Then when the stars lose their lights
  77,9,And when Furijat the heaven
  77,10,And when the mountains are blown away
  77,11,And when the Messengers are Uqqitat
  77,12,For what Day are these signs postponed
  77,13,For the Day of Sorting Out (the men of Paradise from the men destined for Hell)
  77,14,And what will explain to you what is the Day of Sorting Out
  77,15,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,16,Did We not destroy the ancients
  77,17,So shall We make later generations to follow them
  77,18,Thus do We deal with the criminals
  77,19,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,20,Did We not create you from a despised water
  77,21,Then We placed it in a place of safety
  77,22,For a known period
  77,23,So We did measure; and We are the best to measure
  77,24,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,25,Have We not made the earth Kifat (a receptacle)
  77,26,For the living and the dead
  77,27,"And have placed therein fixed towers, and have given you Furat water"
  77,28,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,29,"(It will be said to the disbelievers): \"Depart you to that which you used to deny"
  77,30,Depart you to a shadow in three columns
  77,31,Neither shady nor of any use against the fierce flame of the Fire
  77,32,"Verily, it (Hell) throws sparks (huge) as Al-Qasr"
  77,33,As if they were Sufr camels
  77,34,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,35,That will be a Day when they shall not speak (during some part of it)
  77,36,And they will not be permitted to put forth any excuse
  77,37,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,38,That will be a Day of Decision! We have brought you and the men of old together
  77,39,"So, if you have a plot, use it against Me (Allah)"
  77,40,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,41,"Verily, those who had Taqwa, shall be amidst shades and springs"
  77,42,"And fruits, such as they desire"
  77,43,Eat and drink comfortably for that which you used to do
  77,44,"Verily, thus We reward the Muhsinin"
  77,45,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,46,"Eat and enjoy yourselves for a little while. Verily, you are criminals"
  77,47,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,48,"And when it is said to them: \"Bow down yourself!\" They bow not down"
  77,49,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,50,Then in what statement after this will they believe